---
layout: layout-base.njk
pagination:
  data: cropCitySummaries
  size: 1
  alias: pageData
permalink: "{{ pageData.url }}index.html"
eleventyComputed:
  title: "{{ pageData.cropName }} in {{ pageData.cityName }} | Planting Dates & Maturity Guide"
  description: "{{ pageData.cropName }} planting timing, frost dates, and maturity outlook for {{ pageData.cityName }}, {{ pageData.regionName }}."
  canonical: "https://growbydate.com{{ pageData.url }}"
---

{% macro formatMmdd(mmdd) %}
  {% if not mmdd %}
    —
  {% else %}
    {{ mmdd
      | replace("01-", "Jan ")
      | replace("02-", "Feb ")
      | replace("03-", "Mar ")
      | replace("04-", "Apr ")
      | replace("05-", "May ")
      | replace("06-", "Jun ")
      | replace("07-", "Jul ")
      | replace("08-", "Aug ")
      | replace("09-", "Sep ")
      | replace("10-", "Oct ")
      | replace("11-", "Nov ")
      | replace("12-", "Dec ")
      | replace("-0", " ")
      | replace("-", " ")
    }}
  {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

<header class="header">
  <h1>When to Plant {{ pageData.cropName }} in {{ pageData.cityName }}</h1>
  <p class="lede">{{ pageData.lede }}</p>
</header>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Can {{ pageData.cropName }} Mature in {{ pageData.cityName }}?</h2>

  {% if pageData.fit.confidence == "strong" %}
  <p>
    In a typical year, {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} usually mature reliably in {{ pageData.cityName }}. Most gardeners have enough seasonal heat to work with and good flexibility in both timing and variety choice.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "good" %}
  <p>
    In a typical year, {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} usually mature well in {{ pageData.cityName }}, though results still depend on planting at the right time and choosing varieties suited to the local season.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "borderline" %}
  <p>
    In a typical year, {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} can mature in {{ pageData.cityName }}, but the season does not leave much margin for delay or slower varieties. Earlier choices and warmer sites make a noticeable difference.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "risky" %}
  <p>
    In a typical year, {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} are difficult to finish reliably in {{ pageData.cityName }}. The season usually favors only the fastest varieties, especially when planted in warm, protected sites.
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="tableWrap">
    <table class="table">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Typical Outlook</strong></td>
          <td><strong>{{ pageData.fit.confidence | capitalize }}</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Crop GDD Target</td>
          <td>{{ pageData.crop.gddTargetTypical }}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Available GDD from Planting</td>
          <td>{{ pageData.fit.availableGddFromPlanting }}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Typical First Fall Frost</td>
          <td>{{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.fall50) }}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Typical Frost-Free Days</td>
          <td>{{ pageData.frost.frostFreeDays }}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top:0.9rem;">
    In practical terms, {{ pageData.cityName }} usually sees a last spring frost around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.spring50) }} and a first fall frost around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.frost.fall50) }}, creating a typical frost-free window of about {{ pageData.frost.frostFreeDays }} days.
  </p>

  {% if pageData.fit.heatMarginSentence %}
  <p class="small">
    {{ pageData.fit.heatMarginSentence }}
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.regionalComparisonSentence %}
  <p class="small">
    {{ pageData.fit.regionalComparisonSentence }}
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% include "region/modules/simple-city-crop-planting-window.njk" %}

  {% if pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate %}
  <p>
    Gardeners usually start indoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.startIndoorsDate) }}
    {% if pageData.planting.plantOutDate %}and plant outdoors around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.plantOutDate) }}{% endif %}.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.planting.directSowDate %}
  <p>
    Planting usually begins around {{ formatMmdd(pageData.planting.directSowDate) }}.
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Growing {{ pageData.cropName }} Successfully in {{ pageData.cityName }}</h2>

  {% if pageData.advisory %}
  <p>{{ pageData.advisory.succeed }}</p>
  <p>{{ pageData.advisory.fail }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h3>Best {{ pageData.cropName }} to Grow Based on Climate Data</h3>

  {% if pageData.fit.confidence == "strong" %}
  <p>
    Most {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} varieties can succeed in {{ pageData.cityName }} in a typical year. Gardeners usually have enough seasonal heat to grow both faster and midseason types without pushing the limits of the season.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "good" %}
  <p>
    In {{ pageData.cityName }}, many {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} varieties work well when planted on time. Faster and midseason types are usually the most dependable choices.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "borderline" %}
  <p>
    In {{ pageData.cityName }}, earlier {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} varieties are usually the safest choice because they need less time and heat to finish before fall frost.
  </p>
  {% elif pageData.fit.confidence == "risky" %}
  <p>
    In {{ pageData.cityName }}, earlier {{ pageData.cropName | lower }} varieties are usually the only reliable choice. Larger and later types often run out of season before finishing well.
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed and pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed.length %}
  <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
    Gardeners often look to varieties such as:
  </p>

  <ul style="margin-top:0.45rem;">
    {% for v in pageData.fit.fittingVarietyExamplesDetailed %}
      <li><strong>{{ v.name }}</strong> — {{ v.note }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.copy.commonFailureMode %}
  <p class="small muted">
    Main risk: {{ pageData.copy.commonFailureMode }}
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  <h4>How Microclimates Affect {{ pageData.cropName }}</h4>

  {% if pageData.advisory %}
  <p>{{ pageData.advisory.micro }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if pageData.advisory and pageData.advisory.localInterpretation %}
  <p class="small">
    {{ pageData.advisory.localInterpretation }}
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

{% include "crop-city/modules/city-crop-links.njk" %}

<p class="small muted" style="margin-top:1rem;">
  For a broader local overview, see the
  <a href="/planting-dates/{% if pageData.country == 'canada' %}canada/{% endif %}{{ pageData.regionKey }}/{{ pageData.cityKey }}/">
    {{ pageData.cityName }} planting guide
  </a>.
  You can also use the <a href="/tools/growing-degree-day-planner/">Growing Degree Day Planner</a> to test planting dates and crop timing.
</p>